That's good, I'll make this constants below ..

It seems to me a little bit more models oriented this type of data.   Thoughts?

// cannot have "-" in the namespace
// this I am not sure we should fix in a enum.  
// Thoughts?
PROMETHEUS_NAMESPACE = enum { "api", "pap", "distribution", "pdpa", "pdpx", "pdpd" }   

// prometheus library will generate for counters of the form:
// <PROMETHEUS_NAMESPACE>_<PROMETHEUS_COUNTER_DEPLOY_REQUESTS>_total

PROMETHEUS_DEPLOY_METRIC = "policy_deploy_requests"

// these labels can be applied to any object
PROMETHEUS_OPERATION_LABEL = "operation"
PROMETHEUS_STATE_LABEL = "state"  
PROMETHEUS_STATUS_LABEL = "status"    

// The operation values not need to be defined and can be retrieve 
// from policy/models:

org.onap.policy.models.pdp.enums.PdpResponseStatus
org.onap.policy.models.pdp.enums.PdpState

PROMETHEUS_OPERATION_VALUES = enum { "deploy", "undeploy" }

Let's just focus on metrics deploy/undeploy oriented for this exercise.
Comments?

Thanks Rashmi!   With regards to state, I think in terms of selection, you can leave in or out in a query to narrow the query down by it or not.   In some cases, it may provide important information as deploying policies in PASSIVE state is not the same as in ACTIVE in the sense that they are not functional yet, so that would be there if anybody needs more granularity in the selection.    To make it clear, the state is no mandatory and can be omitted, it may not make much sense for example in distribution.

I think for the policy execution counters, the state values would be up to PDP to choose the right values for the labels, I don't think we need to standardize on it.  I think though querying the execution counter aggregating all labels should give the total (can apply the sum or rate for that). In the drools pdp, we'll peg transactions and operations, under some category but I still need to look at that based on the information available.

As an FYI, this is how the prometheus folks defined their http requests counter with at least 4 labels:

prometheus_http_requests_total{code="200", handler="/api/v1/alertmanagers", instance="localhost:9090", job="prometheus"}
	1
prometheus_http_requests_total{code="200", handler="/api/v1/label/:name/values", instance="localhost:9090", job="prometheus"}
	16
prometheus_http_requests_total{code="200", handler="/api/v1/metadata", instance="localhost:9090", job="prometheus"}
	7
